p2
VShowcase of promise
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe second anniversary of Chamber of Music, an association of learners of carnatic music under the tutelage of Pantula Rama and her husband M.S.N. Murty (noted vocalists and violinists) was celebrated at Srikrishna ashram last weekend. Recitals of one-hour duration by juniors followed by full-fledged concerts by seniors marked the two evenings.Young S. Pardhiva in the company of master Jayadeep Sarma on mridangam renderingGirirajasuthatanaya(Bangala),Sudhamayi(Amrithavarshini) andParidaanamichithe(Bilhari) adorned with aalapana and swaram held high promise.Featured next, Bhavaraju Lakshmi Surya Teja in the company of her guru Rama on violin and D. Dharmarao on mridangam rendered a melodious vocal recital. Besides elaboratingTulasidalamulache(Mayamalavagoula) she rendered ragam , tanam and pallavi in Bhairavi in Trisratriputa with the poorvangam set in misra and the uttarangam in trisragathi with consummate finish like a professional.Dwaram V.K.G. Thyagaraju knowledgeably and tunefully renderingBhairaviAtathalavarnam(Viriboni) followed byBhajare Vinayakam(Hamsadhvani) and expansively expatiatingAaragimpave(Todi) aesthetically proved his mettle as a vocalist. G.V.S. Raghuram on violin and M. Kamesh on mridangam lent good support.The grand finale of the two-day fete was the violin recital by Ivaturi Vijayeswara Rao in the company of Ch. Ramya Kiranmayi on another violin and P. Jayadev on mridangam. He got off to a scholarly start playingGhanaraagapanchaka taanam. Then he renderedSrivaralakshmi(Sri),Telisiramachintana(Purnachandrika),Raminchuvaarevarura(Suposhini) and an eruditely structured ragam, taanam and pallavi inGowrimanohariin Aaditalam before concluding the recital with a padam in Janjhuti.
